# Backend Rules

Stack: Python, FastAPI, Pydantic. Future: SQLAlchemy or Supabase client, Celery/RQ for jobs.

## Structure

- `routers/` — thin HTTP layer only
- `services/` — business logic
- `adapters/` — external systems (inventory sources, ESL providers)
- `schemas/` — Pydantic request/response models
- `models/` — database models (when added)
- `workers/` — async job handlers (when added)

## Patterns

- `VehicleService` and `SyncEngine` produce `LabelPayload` and sync jobs only—they never call Minew or any provider directly.
- All inventory sources implement `InventoryAdapter` and return `NormalizedVehicle`.
- All ESL hardware calls go through `RendererAdapter` then `TransportAdapter`.
- Enforce dealership scope in every service method once auth exists.
- Add audit logs on every data-changing operation.

## API Conventions

- Base path: `/api/v1` (when versioned routes are added)
- Health check: `GET /health` returns `{"status": "ok"}`
- Keep provider credentials server-side only; never expose in responses.

## Tests

Place tests in `app/tests/`. Cover pairing rules and price-update flows when those features land.
